    &lt;Title&gt;Fantastic &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Richard L&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I underwent a double hernia operation at Tees Valley Hospital and cannot recommend the hospital and its staff highly enough.

I was so well looked after by fantastic staff. From the surgical and clinical teams through to the chef and cleaning staff, all were thoroughly professional and the care I received was first rate.

I was kept in overnight and nothing was too much trouble for any of the nurses and doctors that looked after me. The facilities are brand new and spotless. It was the best experience one could hope for in a hospital from arrival through to a very thorough discharge.

I was put at ease by friendly staff and felt I was in the best possible hands all the way way through my stay. Everyone came across that the genuinely enjoyed working there which made such a difference to the care received.

Thank you to everyone who looked after me.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
